# AI Hedge Fund Project Rules for Cursor

## Environment Setup
- This project uses Poetry for dependency management
- Python interpreter: C:\Users\Admin\AppData\Local\pypoetry\Cache\virtualenvs\ai-hedge-fund-Dot02FSf-py3.13\Scripts\python.exe
- Always use `poetry run` prefix for running Python scripts
- Source code is in the `src/` directory

## Package Management
- Dependencies are managed in `pyproject.toml`
- Use `poetry add <package>` to add new dependencies
- Use `poetry install` to install all dependencies
- Never use `pip install` directly

## Code Style
- Use Black for code formatting
- Use Flake8 for linting
- Follow PEP 8 guidelines
- Use type hints where possible

## Project Structure
- Main source code: `src/`
- Tests: `tests/`
- Data: `data/`
- Documentation: `docs/`
- Junk files: `junk/` (excluded from analysis)

## Database
- Primary database: `data/comprehensive_equity.duckdb`
- Options data table: `options_chain_data`
- Use DuckDB for all database operations

## Running Scripts
- Always use: `poetry run python <script>`
- For modules: `poetry run python -m <module>`
- For tests: `poetry run pytest`

## Environment Variables
- Set PYTHONPATH=./src
- Use .env file for configuration (if needed)
